content:
Can you provide me with more detailed list, which sub-styles you didnt mention in your answears, start from the Abstract Expression and continue with Indigenous Art (various styles from Indigenous cultures around the world):

Native American Plains, Native American Southwest, Native American Woodlands, Inuit Sculpture, Pacific Northwest Coast
African Art (including traditional and contemporary styles):

Dogon Mask, Yoruba Textile, Bantu Pottery, Ndebele Beadwork, Ashanti Gold
Oceanic Art (including traditional and contemporary styles from Pacific Islands):

Maori Tattoo, Hawaiian Quilt, Samoan Tapa, Tongan Mat, Fijian Dagger
Pre-Columbian Art (from indigenous cultures in the Americas before European contact):

Maya Sculpture, Aztec Calendar, Inca Textile, Moche Ceramic, Nazca Line
Islamic Art (including calligraphy, architecture, and decorative arts):
Ottoman Tiles, Persian Miniature, Mughal Miniature, Timurid Architecture, Fatimid Rock crystal
